This README file contains information on the contents of the Fast-Boot project. Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============================================
Before you begin, ensure that you have built the BSP first.

You can do this by running the following command:

$ bitbake imx-image-multimedia


Setup Environment
============================================
To set up the environment for Fast Boot, you need to copy all patch and shell files to the appropriate build directory.

Use the following command:

$ cp Fast-Boot/* ../bld-<backend>/

Make sure to replace <backend> with the actual backend you are using.


Build Fast Boot
============================================
To build Fast Boot, execute the following command:

$ sh ./Build-Fast-Boot.sh

For more command details and options available in the Build-Fast-Boot.sh script, you can use the help command:

$ sh ./Build-Fast-Boot.sh help

This will display a list of available commands and their descriptions.


Additional Information
============================================
Ensure you have the necessary permissions to execute the script.
Running the clean option will reset any uncommitted changes in the specified components. Use it with caution.
Make sure to run this script from the correct directory where the build environment is set up.
If you encounter any issues, please refer to the troubleshooting section in the documentation or contact the support team.
Thank you for using Fast-Boot! We hope this project helps you streamline your boot process.
